text: Liemers is a South Guelderish dialect, which is a Low Franconian sub-dialect. It is spoken in the Liemers, a region in the province of Gelderland, the Netherlands. Liemers has some influences from neighbouring Achterhooks, which is a Low Saxon dialect. Category:West Germanic languages Category:Languages of the Netherlands Category:Liemers
title: Liemers (dialect)
